---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import bandPhoto from '../assets/band-group.jpg';
---
<section class="relative overflow-hidden border-t border-white/5 py-28" id="about">
  <div class="mesh-gradient"></div>
  <div class="relative z-10 mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6">
    <span class="section-label section-label-anim">About</span>
    <h2 class="section-label-anim mb-12 font-serif text-3xl leading-tight sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl">
      From <span class="text-crimson-500">Monterrey</span> to the World
    </h2>

    <!-- Band photo -->
    <div class="reveal mb-16 overflow-hidden rounded-2xl">
      <Image
        src={bandPhoto}
        alt="The Warning — the Villarreal Vélez sisters"
        class="h-64 w-full object-cover object-top sm:h-80 md:h-96"
        loading="lazy"
        decoding="async"
        widths={[640, 1024, 1600]}
      />
    </div>

    <div class="reveal grid gap-12 md:grid-cols-2">
      <div>
        <h3 class="mb-4 text-xl font-semibold">The Beginning</h3>
        <p class="leading-relaxed text-text-secondary">
          The sisters all received classical piano training from a young age. After years
          playing <em>Rock Band</em> at home, Daniela chose guitar, Paulina chose drums,
          and seven-year-old Alejandra picked up the bass. In 2013, the power trio was born.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed text-text-secondary">
          In 2014, their YouTube cover of Metallica's "Enter Sandman" went viral, amassing
          over 26 million views. Metallica guitarist Kirk Hammett himself praised Paulina:
          <em class="text-crimson-400">"The drummer kicks maximum ass!"</em>
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="mb-4 text-xl font-semibold">The Rise</h3>
        <p class="leading-relaxed text-text-secondary">
          After appearing on <em>The Ellen DeGeneres Show</em> in 2015 and earning
          scholarships to Berklee College of Music, the band built a fiercely loyal fanbase.
          They signed with Lava / Republic Records in 2020 and have since released four
          studio albums, toured with Muse, Foo Fighters, and Guns N' Roses, and earned a
          Latin GRAMMY nomination.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed text-text-secondary">
          In 2025, the band sold out three nights at Mexico City's 10,000-capacity
          Auditorio Nacional — a milestone that led to their first concert film,
          <em>Live from Auditorio Nacional, CDMX</em>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
